What's adapted vs. dropped
--------------------------

Kept from musl:
- The algorithms themselves — every one-liner trick (the
  ((unsigned)c-'0') range check, the (c|32) case-fold, the
  c & 0x5f / c | 32 toupper/tolower implementations).
- The function signatures and ASCII semantics.

Dropped:
- musl's locale-aware variants (`__isdigit_l`, etc.) and the
  `weak_alias(...)` glue around them.  This library is C-locale
  only.
- Wide-character counterparts (`iswalpha` etc.) — out of scope
  for a teaching libc.
- Multi-platform headers (`<ctype.h>` → `<bits/...>`).  Here
  everything lives in one small header.
